content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 441.310 - Services

State Regulations
(a) Sold services
refers to ancillary services a hospital sells to other providers of health care
services, rather than directly to the other provider's patients. (b) It may also refer to other operating
expenses, (i.e., laundry, data processing, etc.) which you sell to another
organization (health care provider or commercial enterprise). Notes
